{
  "doc_id": "34404",
  "text": "Lay people are increasingly adopting HBPM. A UK survey among a randomly selected sample showed that 9% of respondents had self-tested their BP [CITATION_1] . The percentage increases considerably among hypertensive adults: 31% and 43% of the respondents in cross-sectional studies in the UK [CITATION_2] and US [CITATION_3] respectively reported to having measured their own BP.",
